1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:02,560
You did amazing today, little director.

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:03,932
I trusted you today.

3
00:00:03,932 --> 00:00:05,150
Trust you with what?

4
00:00:05,150 --> 00:00:09,760
Trust me to take care of you
as your boyfriend.

5
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:13,172
I'm glad you and Aurora made up.

6
00:00:13,172 --> 00:00:15,360
It's all thanks to Sun.

7
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:16,684
Which one is that?

8
00:00:16,684 --> 00:00:18,960
This one.

9
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:22,030
Isn't this Teacher Solar?

10
00:00:22,030 --> 00:00:23,740
Sun?

11
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,480
[Class 2/1]

12
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:41,656
The English class play results are out.

13
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:46,440
We won first place!

14
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:49,802
Yay!

15
00:00:49,802 --> 00:00:54,262
You guys were amazing,
so I got you something.

16
00:00:56,652 --> 00:00:58,622
Here.

17
00:00:58,622 --> 00:01:02,288
I printed these photos
for you to keep as a memory.

18
00:01:02,288 --> 00:01:07,424
So you'll remember
we did something fun together.

19
00:01:08,622 --> 00:01:12,182
Wait. What about Sun's photo?

20
00:01:12,182 --> 00:01:14,472
The secret one comes last!

21
00:01:14,472 --> 00:01:16,744
Come get yours.

22
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:21,140
Here you go.

23
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:22,668
Here.

24
00:01:32,450 --> 00:01:34,050
If things keep going like this,

25
00:01:34,050 --> 00:01:36,620
we probably don't have to worry
about Sun anymore.

26
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:38,668
That's a relief.

27
00:01:38,668 --> 00:01:42,300
By the way, how's your guitar practice going?

28
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,140
Have you started yet?

29
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,230
You haven't?

30
00:01:49,230 --> 00:01:50,620
What are you waiting for?

31
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:55,154
Well, I'm already exhausted
from teaching the kids.

32
00:01:55,154 --> 00:01:56,560
Give me a break.

33
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,615
That's exactly why
you need to hurry up and practice

34
00:01:58,615 --> 00:02:00,124
so you can take a long break.

35
00:02:00,124 --> 00:02:03,748
Or do you want to keep dealing with Sun
every other day?

36
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:06,640
Do you want me to help you practice?

37
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:10,142
It's okay. I can manage on my own.

38
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:13,240
You might want to hurry,

39
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:16,650
because in the parent group chat I'm in,

40
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:19,484
they're starting to get suspicious about Sun.

41
00:02:19,484 --> 00:02:21,800
It could blow up into a school-wide issue.

42
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,962
But no matter what,

43
00:02:22,962 --> 00:02:28,508
I'm sure
our acting principal can handle the chaos.

44
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:31,720
My kid has been complaining

45
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:34,280
that the food at school
isn't really to their taste.

46
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,780
Please look into this, Principal.

47
00:02:36,780 --> 00:02:39,940
Of course. I'll handle it.

48
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:42,644
Could you please check
the school supply purchase documents?

49
00:02:42,644 --> 00:02:45,508
Of course. Let me handle it.

50
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:46,960
[Ms. Pang (The Picky One)]

51
00:02:57,830 --> 00:03:00,148
Still sure about that?

52
00:03:58,190 --> 00:04:00,730
I made it through another day.

53
00:04:00,730 --> 00:04:03,500
You're pretty hardworking, huh?

54
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,960
You always take all the problems on yourself.

55
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:09,910
Wanna try letting others help for a change?

56
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:11,400
Listen, Teacher Jee.

57
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:15,280
I take on these problems
because it's my responsibility.

58
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:20,068
It's not right to burden other people, is it?

59
00:04:20,068 --> 00:04:22,870
If you need to vent,

60
00:04:23,588 --> 00:04:26,000
you can always vent to the two of us.

61
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,910
That's exactly what I need.

62
00:04:28,910 --> 00:04:31,680
My spiritual journey is beginning.

63
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:39,450
Just think of it as nourishing my soul.

64
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:44,716
Basically, he'll be dumping
his work on me for months.

65
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:49,796
Miss Fresh, I'm sure you'll grow from this.

66
00:04:49,796 --> 00:04:51,549
Goodbye.

67
00:04:52,550 --> 00:04:54,964
Grow from this? My ass!

68
00:04:54,964 --> 00:04:56,820
He's clearly just dumping
all this crap on me!

69
00:04:56,820 --> 00:05:00,732
Oh, my inner voice is getting so loud
these days.

70
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:04,730
Gosh, I'm so freaking annoyed!

71
00:05:04,730 --> 00:05:07,196
How can someone just leave their job
for that long?

72
00:05:07,196 --> 00:05:12,730
Isn't what Principal Maximoff is doing
a violation of employment law?

73
00:05:12,730 --> 00:05:14,476
How could the main campus let this slide?

74
00:05:14,476 --> 00:05:17,520
The main campus is actually
letting it happen.

75
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,380
Wait, no.

76
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:23,580
I think it was Ms. Pang who approved this.

77
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:27,620
Ms. Pang, who you said is
the main campus' stickler?

78
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:30,380
Super strict. Always gets what she wants.

79
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:31,724
Double standards?

80
00:05:31,724 --> 00:05:33,690
No.

81
00:05:33,690 --> 00:05:34,836
Not double.

82
00:05:34,836 --> 00:05:36,836
Ten standards.

83
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:42,068
Oh, I'm so glad people are talking about me.

84
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:47,440
Ms. Pang.

85
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:50,316
It's been a while, Principal Sodchuen.

86
00:05:50,316 --> 00:05:53,000
Wait, no.

87
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:57,100
Acting Principal Sodchuen.

88
00:06:08,710 --> 00:06:10,400
What are you guys doing?

89
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,840
Ms. Pang came to school without notice.

90
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:17,812
What?
Ms. Pang, the main campus representative?

91
00:06:17,812 --> 00:06:19,668
Please don't worry, Ms. Pang.

92
00:06:19,668 --> 00:06:21,556
While I've been Acting Principal,

93
00:06:21,556 --> 00:06:25,668
I've been sending regular email updates
to Principal Maximoff.

94
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,021
I'm well aware of that,

95
00:06:30,021 --> 00:06:34,114
but I'm here today
because something caught my attention,

96
00:06:34,114 --> 00:06:37,132
and I'd like to look into it.

97
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:46,720
This is Teacher Solar, isn't it?

98
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,110
Yes.

99
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:49,410
Why?

100
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:51,972
Several parents have reported

101
00:06:51,972 --> 00:06:54,960
that this teacher often behaves like a child,

102
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,720
claiming it's role-play,

103
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:00,452
and often says bad things to the kids.

104
00:07:00,452 --> 00:07:04,710
It's quite an interesting matter, isn't it?

105
00:07:04,710 --> 00:07:06,720
Yes.

106
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:10,380
May I know where Teacher Solar is?

107
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:11,988
May I see him?

108
00:07:11,988 --> 00:07:15,548
I'd like to have a little chat with him.

109
00:07:15,548 --> 00:07:20,684
Unfortunately, Teacher Solar has a free period
this afternoon,

110
00:07:20,684 --> 00:07:25,106
so he asked me for permission
to go out for personal errands.

111
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,920
That's alright.

112
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,689
I may not see him today,

113
00:07:29,689 --> 00:07:34,332
but I'll certainly see him
on the annual school inspection day.

114
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:37,908
Please excuse me.

115
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,684
Let me walk you out.

116
00:07:43,684 --> 00:07:44,828
Here.

117
00:07:44,828 --> 00:07:47,036
Please, go ahead.

118
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:58,430
Hey, what are you guys doing?

119
00:07:58,430 --> 00:08:03,284
Sodchuen, what should we do now?

120
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,550
Teacher Jee,

121
00:08:05,550 --> 00:08:07,332
please inform all the teachers immediately

122
00:08:07,332 --> 00:08:09,356
to make sure everything is
as ready as possible.

123
00:08:09,356 --> 00:08:12,612
I'm sure Ms. Pang will move up
the annual inspection.

124
00:08:12,612 --> 00:08:14,164
Noted!

125
00:08:18,150 --> 00:08:22,740
Pobmek, this is not an order, but a plea.

126
00:08:22,740 --> 00:08:26,460
Please work on your guitar
as soon as you can.

127
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:31,148
I'm begging you,
so that Solar can get back to being Solar.

128
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:35,492
Okay.

129
00:08:35,492 --> 00:08:37,440
I'm counting on you.

130
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:06,148
Pobmek, why are you even doing this?

131
00:09:06,148 --> 00:09:10,240
I didn't send you to school
for this kind of thing.

132
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,760
How's it going?

133
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,468
Are you getting the hang of it now?

134
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:24,120
Hey. I'm sorry.

135
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:26,840
I just got excited.

136
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,708
It's alright,

137
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:39,676
Take your time, okay?

138
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,508
Yup.

139
00:09:49,170 --> 00:09:52,000
Let's go. Lunch break is over.

140
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,440
- Let's get ready to teach.
- Jeez! I can't get up!

141
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,640
Help me.

142
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,476
What are you talking about? Let's go.
Come on!

143
00:09:59,476 --> 00:10:01,220
I need a Solar fix.

144
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,640
Hey!

145
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:05,510
Hey! We're outside!

146
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:06,600
No!

147
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,240
Come on, let's go!

148
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,360
[Kiss Voucher]
[1 kiss/hour]

149
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,626
Are you really going to use that here?

150
00:10:28,602 --> 00:10:30,218
Hey!

151
00:10:30,218 --> 00:10:33,474
Are you two in a BL series?

152
00:10:34,430 --> 00:10:37,258
Hey! No teasing!

153
00:10:37,258 --> 00:10:39,122
Why aren't you in class?

154
00:10:39,122 --> 00:10:40,274
Why are you hiding here?

155
00:10:40,274 --> 00:10:41,778
I don't understand anything anyway.

156
00:10:41,778 --> 00:10:44,466
The class is so boring.

157
00:10:44,466 --> 00:10:46,058
Yeah.

158
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:50,130
I know how you feel.

159
00:10:50,130 --> 00:10:52,306
I went through the same thing as a kid.

160
00:10:52,306 --> 00:10:55,522
Right, Teacher? Math is so not fun.

161
00:10:55,522 --> 00:10:58,426
I know, right? How can math be...

162
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:02,602
Hey! That's my subject!

163
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:09,830
No!

164
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:12,050
Hey! Are you going to write me up?

165
00:11:12,050 --> 00:11:14,370
No, no, no, no!

166
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:18,002
No!

167
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,410
Stop teasing the kids.

168
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,980
Of course.

169
00:11:27,980 --> 00:11:31,514
I'll look into it as soon as possible.

170
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:08,300
Thank god you found out in advance
that Ms. Pang is coming tomorrow.

171
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:11,740
And luckily, tomorrow is Solar's day.

172
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:13,346
Good.

173
00:12:15,990 --> 00:12:20,160
This is my first year being at school
during inspection day.

174
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:22,050
I'm pretty nervous.

175
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:25,818
It's not just you. I'm nervous too.

176
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:30,978
I think someone's even more nervous
than we are.

177
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:36,298
Hey, are you really a P.E. teacher?

178
00:12:36,298 --> 00:12:38,450
That little run
already got you out of breath.

179
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:44,594
Stop teasing me. We're in big trouble.

180
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:01,314
Ms. Pang, are you here on business?

181
00:13:01,314 --> 00:13:04,490
This is quite sudden.

182
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:08,530
I'm here to do the inspection today instead.

183
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:10,794
Oh, welcome.

184
00:13:10,794 --> 00:13:13,110
Our school is always ready.

185
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:16,362
We just did a clean-up together, right?

186
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:19,010
No wonder I can smell it.

187
00:13:19,010 --> 00:13:21,314
Does it really smell that clean?

188
00:13:21,314 --> 00:13:23,618
Smells like it's just for show.

189
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:32,034
Actually, we help each other
clean like this every week.

190
00:13:32,034 --> 00:13:33,250
Oh?

191
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,938
Please come in, Ms. Pang.

192
00:13:35,938 --> 00:13:38,034
All the teachers are ready to welcome you.

193
00:13:38,034 --> 00:13:42,066
Aren't we going to welcome the parents
as well?

194
00:13:47,540 --> 00:13:49,810
May I ask why you're here?

195
00:13:49,810 --> 00:13:50,970
Of course, we had to come.

196
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:53,394
Someone said
there's a parents' meeting today.

197
00:13:53,394 --> 00:13:56,410
A meeting? There isn't one.

198
00:13:56,410 --> 00:13:58,680
If there were, I'd know.

199
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,430
[Urgent Parents' Meeting at 11 AM tomorrow
- Ms. Pang]

200
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,080
Here.

201
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:07,363
There must be some misunderstanding.

202
00:14:07,965 --> 00:14:09,810
I didn't receive that message.

203
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:11,658
Of course, you didn't.

204
00:14:11,658 --> 00:14:15,770
Ms. Pang created that group chat,
and you're not in it, Principal.

205
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:22,866
Parents, please come in.

206
00:14:34,430 --> 00:14:35,690
Solar!

207
00:14:35,690 --> 00:14:36,900
I'm Pobmek.

208
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:41,740
No, I mean go take Solar home now!

209
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:43,474
- Solar!
- Go!

210
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:54,890
We use the sprinklers
to water the trees every morning.

211
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:56,266
It saves a lot of work.

212
00:14:56,266 --> 00:14:59,682
Let me get straight to
what I'm concerned about.

213
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:04,088
Who's Sun?

214
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,230
Sun, let's go!

215
00:15:07,230 --> 00:15:08,042
- What?
- Let's go.

216
00:15:08,042 --> 00:15:09,226
- What, Uncle?
- Oh.

217
00:15:09,226 --> 00:15:14,138
I think that's just a nickname
the teacher and students use playfully.

218
00:15:14,138 --> 00:15:15,866
It's probably nothing important.

219
00:15:15,866 --> 00:15:18,018
Where are we going?

220
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:27,754
Teacher.

221
00:15:32,530 --> 00:15:34,178
What's going on, Uncle?

222
00:15:34,178 --> 00:15:35,210
Why did you drag me here?

223
00:15:35,210 --> 00:15:37,070
Keep quiet, Sun!

224
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,450
I have a big secret to tell you.

225
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:43,786
You see that woman?

226
00:15:43,786 --> 00:15:44,780
Yeah.

227
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:47,154
Actually, she's a witch.

228
00:15:47,154 --> 00:15:48,618
Huh?

229
00:15:49,306 --> 00:15:51,218
She disguises herself during the day,

230
00:15:51,218 --> 00:15:52,706
plotting to take the kids' hearts.

231
00:15:52,706 --> 00:15:54,722
Huh? Seriously?

232
00:15:54,722 --> 00:15:55,790
Yes!

233
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:57,610
We have to hide from that auntie.

234
00:15:57,610 --> 00:16:00,310
We cannot let her find us.

235
00:16:00,310 --> 00:16:01,990
Got it?

236
00:16:01,990 --> 00:16:03,490
Okay.

237
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:10,200
What is this violence?

238
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,350
Oh, let me explain.

239
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:15,538
Teacher Jee really loves nature.

240
00:16:15,538 --> 00:16:17,858
Every day after school,

241
00:16:17,858 --> 00:16:21,550
he comes here to lie on the ground
and soak up the sun.

242
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:25,938
Girls, do any of you know Teacher Solar?

243
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:30,986
What's he like?

244
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:36,954
The way you're asking us to help you,

245
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:39,306
and you even brought dessert to convince us.

246
00:16:39,306 --> 00:16:40,954
What do you call this again?

247
00:16:40,954 --> 00:16:44,510
This is called bribery.

248
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:50,780
But it's normal in our country.

249
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:53,578
Girls, please don't think of it that way.

250
00:16:53,578 --> 00:16:56,430
Just think of it as helping each other out.

251
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:59,538
Okay. I want to help Teacher Solar anyway.

252
00:16:59,538 --> 00:17:02,300
What would you like us to do?

253
00:17:04,350 --> 00:17:07,250
Teacher Solar is kind.

254
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,898
He's a good teacher.

255
00:17:08,898 --> 00:17:12,027
We're happy.

256
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:17,540
Is there anything else
you'd like to say about Teacher Solar?

257
00:17:17,540 --> 00:17:20,066
Whoever speaks honestly

258
00:17:20,066 --> 00:17:26,018
will get a reward from me today.

259
00:17:28,090 --> 00:17:31,450
Actually, it's nothing serious.

260
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:34,378
It's just that Teacher Solar
keeps switching back and forth

261
00:17:34,378 --> 00:17:36,764
between acting like a kid and an adult.

262
00:17:37,620 --> 00:17:40,913
Teacher Solar just gets into character,
remember?

263
00:17:40,913 --> 00:17:43,466
But sometimes it's a bit weird.

264
00:17:43,466 --> 00:17:46,458
Maybe there's something
we don't know about him.

265
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:48,146
Like something unusual.

266
00:17:48,146 --> 00:17:51,047
Yeah. Something unusual.

267
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:53,160
Excuse me?

268
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,898
There's a teacher who's unusual?

269
00:17:54,898 --> 00:17:58,430
He's the one I think has a problem.

270
00:17:58,430 --> 00:18:02,790
Girls, has Teacher Solar gone home?

271
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,480
Not yet.

272
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,750
He was just playing with us earlier.

273
00:18:06,750 --> 00:18:08,842
Wow! You're so sweet!

274
00:18:08,842 --> 00:18:11,954
Here's your reward.

275
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:16,482
We should go find Teacher Solar.

276
00:18:16,482 --> 00:18:19,640
I think he's still at school.

277
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,234
Let's go.

278
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:35,000
[Principal Sodchuen: Run!]

279
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:37,794
Let's go!

280
00:19:00,630 --> 00:19:02,250
What should we do?

281
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:04,234
What are you doing, Teacher?

282
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:08,362
Four, King, help me!

283
00:19:08,362 --> 00:19:11,146
What do we get in return?

284
00:19:11,146 --> 00:19:12,470
Hey!

285
00:19:12,470 --> 00:19:14,042
You kids always want something in return!

286
00:19:14,042 --> 00:19:15,300
Come on, Teacher.

287
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:17,450
Just a little snack would be enough for us.

288
00:19:17,450 --> 00:19:18,794
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

289
00:19:18,794 --> 00:19:21,580
I don't have anything to give you right now.
What do you want?

290
00:19:21,580 --> 00:19:24,338
Oh, come on!

291
00:19:27,701 --> 00:19:29,401
Hey!

292
00:19:37,658 --> 00:19:39,986
Why are you hiding over there?

293
00:19:39,986 --> 00:19:44,180
Oh, my shoe's loose.

294
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:03,692
Sun!

295
00:20:07,830 --> 00:20:11,978
Oh, where did Sun and Pobmek go?

296
00:20:11,978 --> 00:20:13,258
I don't know either.

297
00:20:13,258 --> 00:20:15,852
They probably got away and went home.

298
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,200
Teacher Solar has probably really left.

299
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:23,954
I didn't see him
while I was cleaning the school.

300
00:20:25,710 --> 00:20:28,962
That's alright. I can come back another day.

301
00:20:28,962 --> 00:20:32,000
Thank you, Teacher...

302
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,498
Pobmek.

303
00:20:33,498 --> 00:20:36,300
Thank you, Teacher Pobmek.

304
00:20:43,210 --> 00:20:45,642
Teacher Pobmek.

305
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,666
Why haven't I heard your name before?

306
00:20:59,140 --> 00:21:03,986
I'm usually aware of everything
that goes on in this school.

307
00:21:06,690 --> 00:21:11,458
If you don't mind, could we talk for a bit?

308
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:19,906
[Pobmek: Ms. Pang caught me.]

309
00:21:19,906 --> 00:21:23,162
Sodchuen, is something wrong?

310
00:21:33,474 --> 00:21:36,069
What did you study?

311
00:21:38,748 --> 00:21:40,290
Accounting.

312
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:42,570
So you didn't want to be a teacher
in the first place,

313
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:44,810
since you didn't major in education.

314
00:21:44,810 --> 00:21:48,470
Are you qualified enough?

315
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:50,490
I definitely am.

316
00:21:50,490 --> 00:21:54,440
I have the knowledge, the experience,
and the techniques...

317
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:57,600
But the skills
to teach and handle elementary students

318
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,580
are specialized.

319
00:21:59,580 --> 00:22:03,122
That's not what you studied.

320
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:09,670
What about your teaching license?

321
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:11,434
Do you have one?

322
00:22:12,870 --> 00:22:14,026
I'm about to get it.

323
00:22:14,026 --> 00:22:15,554
What?

324
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:20,626
Do you even have a lesson plan
for your students?

325
00:22:20,626 --> 00:22:24,110
Teacher Pobmek has a clear lesson plan.

326
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:27,698
He prepares everything as best as he can
for the kids.

327
00:22:29,853 --> 00:22:31,586
I'm sorry.

328
00:22:31,586 --> 00:22:34,058
What happened to your face?

329
00:22:35,298 --> 00:22:37,110
My face?

330
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,786
What's wrong with it?

331
00:22:40,730 --> 00:22:42,442
Forget it.

332
00:22:46,010 --> 00:22:50,666
Honestly, without a license,
it's already over for you.

333
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,630
What about you, Mr. Jee?

334
00:22:55,630 --> 00:22:57,978
- I have a license.
- You do realize

335
00:22:57,978 --> 00:23:00,938
that having a license doesn't mean
you can get away with this, right?

336
00:23:00,938 --> 00:23:07,458
Protecting Mr. Pobmek like this
violates the teacher's code of ethics.

337
00:23:09,030 --> 00:23:11,634
Hold on, Ms. Pang. I think...

338
00:23:11,634 --> 00:23:15,994
I thought the problem was just Teacher Solar,

339
00:23:15,994 --> 00:23:20,340
but now I see that
no one's doing their jobs properly,

340
00:23:20,340 --> 00:23:22,146
especially you.

341
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:29,870
Don't make me take this
to upper management.

342
00:23:29,870 --> 00:23:35,950
Your last chance is to fire
Teacher Solar and Mr. Pobmek.

343
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:37,066
Hold on.

344
00:23:37,066 --> 00:23:39,002
Isn't that going too far, Ms. Pang?

345
00:23:39,002 --> 00:23:41,830
If you don't follow my recommendation,

346
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:45,098
it will go much further.

347
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:56,026
Just go!

348
00:23:56,026 --> 00:23:57,990
Get out!

349
00:23:57,990 --> 00:24:00,040
It's okay, Sun.

350
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:02,130
The witch is gone.

351
00:24:13,218 --> 00:24:14,334
Yay!

352
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:18,042
We're safe from the witch
and the zombies now!

353
00:24:21,442 --> 00:24:24,261
Yeah.

354
00:24:24,261 --> 00:24:26,030
Everything's back to normal.

355
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:28,490
Let's go home.

356
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:09,098
Sodchuen...

357
00:25:11,790 --> 00:25:15,080
Don't tell me you've been
pacing back and forth in here all night.

358
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,980
Yeah.

359
00:25:16,980 --> 00:25:20,290
I was the cause of everything
that went wrong yesterday.

360
00:25:20,290 --> 00:25:23,090
How could I let it go so easily?

361
00:25:35,634 --> 00:25:37,275
Sodchuen.

362
00:25:39,232 --> 00:25:40,794
I...

363
00:25:42,430 --> 00:25:46,146
I've been thinking about this all night.

364
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:53,706
I've decided to quit.

365
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,330
No, you can't do this.

366
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:23,800
You can't quit.

367
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:26,746
Then you're not quitting either.

368
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:33,110
Sodchuen.

369
00:26:35,068 --> 00:26:37,354
Why are you helping me?

370
00:26:39,930 --> 00:26:43,030
I'm a terrible teacher.

371
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:45,506
The kids don't even like me.

372
00:26:46,218 --> 00:26:48,790
No one wants to learn from me.

373
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:57,898
I don't even know how to be a good teacher.

374
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:06,074
That's not true at all, Pobmek.

375
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:13,562
You're not only a good teacher.

376
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:18,026
You also helped someone else become one.

377
00:27:20,630 --> 00:27:22,378
So, there are four stages.

378
00:27:22,378 --> 00:27:24,858
Young kids are sensorimotor.

379
00:27:24,858 --> 00:27:28,150
Kindergarten kids are preoperational.

380
00:27:28,150 --> 00:27:30,898
Elementary kids are concrete operational.

381
00:27:30,898 --> 00:27:35,034
And teens are formal operational.

382
00:27:36,350 --> 00:27:39,146
Got it, babe?

383
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:47,090
Solar! Are you even listening to me?

384
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:56,538
What are you doing?

385
00:27:57,390 --> 00:28:01,090
I'm helping you study
even though it's not even my major.

386
00:28:01,090 --> 00:28:02,730
Stop it.

387
00:28:02,730 --> 00:28:05,230
You're the one who should stop.

388
00:28:05,230 --> 00:28:08,218
Don't you know that when you're teaching,

389
00:28:09,074 --> 00:28:10,178
you're so sexy?

390
00:28:10,178 --> 00:28:12,629
What's wrong with you, huh?

391
00:28:12,629 --> 00:28:14,394
Get up! Study!

392
00:28:14,394 --> 00:28:17,386
Come on! No!

393
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:21,460
I've been studying since morning.

394
00:28:21,460 --> 00:28:24,474
I'm about to throw up from all these words.

395
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:28,180
- That bad?
- Yeah!

396
00:28:28,180 --> 00:28:30,874
Okay. Wait here.

397
00:28:32,458 --> 00:28:33,986
Where are you going?

398
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:42,466
I've been preparing all this for you,

399
00:28:42,466 --> 00:28:45,270
since I heard you have to
take the certification exam.

400
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:49,986
Whose boyfriend are you? You're so cute.

401
00:28:49,986 --> 00:28:52,790
That's not all, bro.

402
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,520
[Kiss Voucher: 1 kiss/hour]
Ta-da!

403
00:28:56,230 --> 00:28:58,598
- What's this?
- This is to give you a boost

404
00:28:58,598 --> 00:29:00,650
when you're too tired to keep going.

405
00:29:00,650 --> 00:29:02,674
You can use it with me.

406
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:36,460
But there's one condition.

407
00:29:36,460 --> 00:29:39,346
You can only use it once every hour.

408
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,110
And you have to study.

409
00:29:42,110 --> 00:29:44,353
- Got it?
- Yeah.

410
00:29:44,353 --> 00:29:45,762
Okay.

411
00:29:51,306 --> 00:29:53,850
You're even timing how long you study?

412
00:29:53,850 --> 00:29:55,380
That's more like it!

413
00:29:55,380 --> 00:29:56,794
No.

414
00:29:57,480 --> 00:30:01,002
I'm timing how many minutes are left
until I can kiss my boyfriend again.

415
00:30:03,410 --> 00:30:05,274
- Hey!
- Keep studying!

416
00:30:05,274 --> 00:30:06,738
"Keep studying!"

417
00:30:06,738 --> 00:30:08,670
- Are you going to study or not?
- "Are you going to study or not?"

418
00:30:08,670 --> 00:30:16,610
Your support helped Solar
become the teacher he is today.

419
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:21,514
Both Solar and I believe...

420
00:30:22,260 --> 00:30:26,722
that you can do it.

421
00:30:45,330 --> 00:30:50,034
Sodchuen, I'm going to pass
the teacher certification exam.

422
00:30:53,510 --> 00:30:57,180
And I'm going to fight for my students!

423
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:02,550
We're not quitting anymore!

424
00:31:02,550 --> 00:31:04,570
Wow.

425
00:31:07,460 --> 00:31:08,706
I'm going to cry.

426
00:31:08,706 --> 00:31:10,218
Because you're touched by what we said?

427
00:31:10,218 --> 00:31:12,082
Because of these paper scraps!

428
00:31:12,082 --> 00:31:14,890
My OCD is screaming!

429
00:31:17,962 --> 00:31:19,938
Sorry.

430
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:25,950
I'm glad you're not quitting.

431
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:28,440
And that you're determined
to pass the certification exam.

432
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:32,162
And I'm so happy
you're standing up for our students.

433
00:31:32,162 --> 00:31:34,194
Solar, I'm ready to fight.

434
00:31:34,194 --> 00:31:36,190
I'm so fired up!

435
00:31:36,190 --> 00:31:41,234
But I still don't know
what to do with all of this.

436
00:31:42,538 --> 00:31:45,270
No need to worry about that.

437
00:31:45,270 --> 00:31:49,170
I think I have a plan.

438
00:31:56,690 --> 00:31:58,866
Principal Sodchuen called
this urgent meeting.

439
00:31:58,866 --> 00:32:00,826
What do you think it's about?

440
00:32:00,826 --> 00:32:02,874
It can only be about one thing.

441
00:32:02,874 --> 00:32:05,630
Teacher Solar.

442
00:32:06,442 --> 00:32:08,778
There she is.

443
00:32:16,470 --> 00:32:19,030
Hello, everyone.

444
00:32:19,030 --> 00:32:22,840
I've called this urgent meeting

445
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,898
because there's something
I'd like to confirm.

446
00:32:26,650 --> 00:32:31,426
The rumor that one of our teachers
is acting unusually...

447
00:32:33,260 --> 00:32:35,230
is true.

448
00:32:35,230 --> 00:32:36,706
Who is it?

449
00:32:36,706 --> 00:32:37,858
Really?

450
00:32:37,858 --> 00:32:39,186
What does that mean?

451
00:32:39,186 --> 00:32:45,866
And the teacher in question is Teacher Solar.

452
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:53,160
Hello.

453
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:55,314
My name is Solar.

454
00:32:55,314 --> 00:32:58,070
I'm the homeroom teacher of Grade 2, Class 1.

455
00:32:58,070 --> 00:33:02,390
On the day I'm filming this,
I'm my adult self.

456
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:05,018
But on the day of the parents' meeting

457
00:33:05,018 --> 00:33:07,820
where you're watching this clip,

458
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:12,122
I'll be Sun.

459
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:39,711
Hello.

460
00:33:39,711 --> 00:33:42,380
My name is Sun.

461
00:33:42,380 --> 00:33:45,890
I'm 7 years old, in Grade 2 Class 1.

462
00:33:55,810 --> 00:33:58,530
On the days when Solar is his adult self,

463
00:33:58,530 --> 00:34:01,540
he gives his full effort to his work.

464
00:34:01,540 --> 00:34:04,290
He shows up to teach effectively,

465
00:34:04,290 --> 00:34:08,058
and he's loved by both students and teachers.

466
00:34:13,890 --> 00:34:16,270
On the days he's absent,

467
00:34:16,270 --> 00:34:22,610
other teachers take turns
covering his classes.

468
00:34:22,610 --> 00:34:26,370
We may not be able to stop things like this
from happening,

469
00:34:26,370 --> 00:34:30,746
but we can help each other.

470
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:45,642
Actually,
my concern is not only Teacher Solar,

471
00:34:45,642 --> 00:34:47,940
but also Teacher Pobmek.

472
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:51,234
No, I don't think I can call him
a teacher yet,

473
00:34:51,234 --> 00:34:55,590
because he doesn't even have
a teaching license.

474
00:34:55,590 --> 00:34:56,840
Huh?

475
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:59,034
Why's that?

476
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:11,769
I admit it,
and I apologize to all the parents.

477
00:35:11,769 --> 00:35:14,690
It's true that I don't have
a teaching license yet.

478
00:35:14,690 --> 00:35:17,240
Thank you for admitting that,

479
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:21,170
but it'd be better if you resigned,

480
00:35:21,170 --> 00:35:24,461
because disregarding the rules like this

481
00:35:24,461 --> 00:35:26,860
could never make you a good teacher.

482
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:30,234
Auntie Witch, you didn't have to be so harsh
on Teacher Pobmek.

483
00:35:34,210 --> 00:35:35,590
Auntie?

484
00:35:35,590 --> 00:35:37,000
You're calling me Auntie?

485
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:40,860
Teacher Pobmek is kind,
tries his best to teach,

486
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:43,170
and he really cares about us.

487
00:35:43,170 --> 00:35:45,122
If you don't believe me, look at this.

488
00:35:50,140 --> 00:35:53,274
Sun, that notebook is so small.

489
00:35:53,274 --> 00:35:55,602
Who's going to be able to read that?

490
00:35:55,602 --> 00:35:58,400
I thought you get farsighted
when you're older.

491
00:36:00,830 --> 00:36:02,910
What Sun said is true.

492
00:36:02,910 --> 00:36:06,990
Teacher Pobmek works really hard,
and he really cares about us.

493
00:36:06,990 --> 00:36:07,990
Hey!

494
00:36:07,990 --> 00:36:11,322
Are you writing our names down
to tell our parents?

495
00:36:11,322 --> 00:36:12,346
You can't do that!

496
00:36:12,346 --> 00:36:14,790
I'm not writing your names down
to tell your parents.

497
00:36:14,790 --> 00:36:16,810
- I'm going to give you grades.
- What? Really?

498
00:36:16,810 --> 00:36:17,922
You're going easy on us?

499
00:36:17,922 --> 00:36:20,538
Yay!

500
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:22,670
I'm not going easy on you!

501
00:36:22,670 --> 00:36:25,490
I'm going to give you two
some intensive tutoring.

502
00:36:25,490 --> 00:36:27,310
Huh?

503
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:30,034
Once we really paid attention to
what Teacher Pobmek taught us,

504
00:36:30,034 --> 00:36:32,138
- math became super easy.
- Good job!

505
00:36:32,138 --> 00:36:35,820
- Yay!
- Yay!

506
00:36:36,700 --> 00:36:40,296
Teacher Pobmek
and all the other teachers here

507
00:36:40,296 --> 00:36:42,882
work really hard to teach us,

508
00:36:42,882 --> 00:36:45,990
and that makes us want to come to school.

509
00:36:45,990 --> 00:36:51,202
Sweetie, you're just one of
over a hundred students.

510
00:36:51,202 --> 00:36:54,420
I can't just go by your opinion alone.

511
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:55,906
Actually, we can.

512
00:36:55,906 --> 00:36:59,839
The heart of learning is the students, right?

513
00:36:59,839 --> 00:37:02,866
- That's true.
- Agreed.

514
00:37:03,590 --> 00:37:06,722
As the acting principal,

515
00:37:06,722 --> 00:37:13,630
I admit I may have always given in to others,

516
00:37:13,630 --> 00:37:20,170
but this time, let me be selfish for once.

517
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:27,450
I insist that I will not fire Teacher Solar
or Teacher Pobmek.

518
00:37:33,530 --> 00:37:35,920
I agree.

519
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,930
Let's give them a chance.

520
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:45,610
I'm sorry,

521
00:37:45,610 --> 00:37:48,274
but I'm here on behalf of the administration.

522
00:37:48,274 --> 00:37:52,018
I really can't let this slide so easily.

523
00:37:55,820 --> 00:38:02,082
That said, I'll respect your decision,
Acting Principal Sodchuen.

524
00:38:10,100 --> 00:38:11,538
Thank you.

525
00:38:11,538 --> 00:38:13,770
Don't thank me yet.

526
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:15,740
I have one condition.

527
00:38:15,740 --> 00:38:18,790
I'll allow this for one year only.

528
00:38:18,790 --> 00:38:23,914
I hope the teachers with issues
will be able to sort themselves out.

529
00:38:25,706 --> 00:38:28,794
Thank you, Ms. Pang.

530
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:32,150
Thank you, parents.

531
00:38:32,150 --> 00:38:34,810
Thank you,

532
00:38:34,810 --> 00:38:36,962
beautiful Ms. Pang.

533
00:38:40,378 --> 00:38:43,180
Thank you, everyone.

534
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,320
[Teacher Certification Exam Study Guide]

535
00:39:04,380 --> 00:39:06,338
What are you doing?

536
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:10,938
Laundry, of course. Can't you tell?

537
00:39:12,410 --> 00:39:14,060
This is weird.

538
00:39:14,060 --> 00:39:18,186
Well, you've had a long day, Uncle.

539
00:39:18,186 --> 00:39:20,990
So many people were bothering you.

540
00:39:22,710 --> 00:39:25,722
I don't want to make you any more tired.

541
00:39:27,610 --> 00:39:30,218
You've really grown up, huh?

542
00:39:30,218 --> 00:39:32,100
Of course.

543
00:39:32,100 --> 00:39:33,910
I'm all grown up now.

544
00:39:33,910 --> 00:39:36,240
You don't have to tell me what to do.

545
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,074
I can handle things myself.

546
00:39:41,790 --> 00:39:46,026
Besides, you have something else
to do, right?

547
00:39:50,390 --> 00:39:51,882
I can do my own laundry.

548
00:39:51,882 --> 00:39:54,660
You don't need to keep teaching me.

549
00:39:54,660 --> 00:39:57,186
Use that time to practice your guitar.

550
00:40:15,430 --> 00:40:17,554
Come here, you little troublemaker.

551
00:40:18,500 --> 00:40:20,250
Let me hug you.

552
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:37,738
So nice.

553
00:40:39,390 --> 00:40:42,050
I feel twice as encouraged now.

554
00:41:00,190 --> 00:41:04,790
Put the clothes in the machine
and go take a shower.

555
00:41:04,790 --> 00:41:08,674
I know! I said you don't need to teach me.

556
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,680
[Jak - Ka - Jee:
No need to extend your temp license.]

557
00:41:29,680 --> 00:41:31,120
[You've been studying
for your graduate diploma for a year.]

558
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,560
[Just go for the full license mid-year.]

559
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:34,000
[Pobmek: Okay.
Jee, I need your help with something.]

560
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:45,800
[Kiss Voucher]
[1 kiss/hour]

561
00:42:00,940 --> 00:42:03,154
You want to use this again, right?

562
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:08,346
I can save it for later.

563
00:42:13,110 --> 00:42:15,498
Then this time,

564
00:42:16,110 --> 00:42:18,470
I'll give you one for free.

565
00:42:18,470 --> 00:42:23,082
My amazing boyfriend deserves it.

566
00:42:44,910 --> 00:42:46,770
These are in the way.

567
00:43:46,135 --> 00:43:48,600
What? You're at my condo?

568
00:43:48,600 --> 00:43:51,110
Your mom just came to visit.
Why are you so stressed?

569
00:43:51,110 --> 00:43:52,930
I haven't told my mom.

570
00:43:52,930 --> 00:43:56,420
- Hello.
- That I'm dating a guy.

571
00:43:56,420 --> 00:43:58,034
This is just like a BL series!

572
00:43:58,034 --> 00:44:00,442
You two are so cute.

573
00:44:00,442 --> 00:44:02,066
Your mom seems kind.

574
00:44:02,066 --> 00:44:04,730
Aren't you overthinking?

575
00:44:04,730 --> 00:44:07,680
My mom is the reason I feel this way.

576
00:44:07,680 --> 00:44:09,510
I can do it now!

577
00:44:09,510 --> 00:44:12,400
I guess life is like this.

578
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:14,186
There's so much more to learn.

579
00:44:14,186 --> 00:44:15,890
Well said.

